The paper discusses methods for conditional mutual information estimation, which is a topic related to machine learning and information theory. The use of classifiers and generative models suggests that the paper may fall under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the curse of dimensionality, which is a common problem in information theory and signal processing, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses applications such as graphical models, causal learning, feature selection, and time-series analysis, which are all topics related to artificial intelligence and data science, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses conditional independence testing, which is a topic related to statistical inference and hypothesis testing, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
